⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Pavel Smerdyakov
node BKZ · BKZ · ⟦Pavel Smerdyakov:BKZ:88eab1⟧

WHO   — Pavel Smerdyakov — the servant · the shadow · the murderer
WHAT  — Ivan's dark pupil: he takes ‘everything is permitted’ literally, murders the father, and confesses to Ivan before hanging himself.
WHERE — BKZ · The Brothers Karamazov  Framework inputs: The Brothers Karamazov (Dostoevsky, 1880)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because the novel must show the idea's logical hand — the resentful shadow-brother who does what the clean intellect only thought.
HOW   — By a feigned epileptic fit as alibi, a cold reading of Ivan's atheism, and the conviction that he is merely Ivan's instrument.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  You taught me there is no God and all is permitted, brother — I was only your hands; you did the murder in your head, and I did it in the hall.

